    "causal_summary": "A deeper audit of the command tree after the presentation/router split found two consistency defects. First, commit `493b3c822f` (#44) decided the canonical `allowed-tools` form is the fully-qualified `mcp__<server>__<tool>` prefix and applied it to `resume.md` + `search.md`, but seven routers still carry the same bare or mixed MCP names it fixed. Second, the sk-doc `command_template.md` §11 router standard claims all five split families use an identical six-section shape and own `_auto.yaml`/`_confirm.yaml`, which is false: `memory` and `doctor` have no workflow YAML and use different section vocabularies.",
